> Ignoring the values when it is not writeable/exists does not solve the problem of the db having full paths stored and hence will just defer the problem to a later point and lead to even more unexpected results.

@mheon indicated above that this "problem" (saving runtime paths into the db) exist as a workaround for users with broken setups which change XDG_RUNTIME_DIR at runtime.

What kind of unexpected results do you envision happening with my proposal?
